CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 18, 1960, pg. B7 reads: "9. Alberta Thompson, Pittsburgh, representing the Cuban Tourist Commisison [sic], preesnts [sic] the lucky bride and groom, Mr. and Mrs. Clarence Burleigh, who were married on stage in a solemn ceremony at the home show, with an all-expense paid check for a honeymoon in Havana.
TitMainTitle: Mrs. Clarence Burleigh, walking down aisle with father in the Syria Mosque for the 1960 Courier-WAMO Home-A-Rama
